<br>
well, Im sure the obvious choice is anything to do with defensive abilities, us warriors are not meant to do that much damage anyway, but what I am mostly curious about.  Are there any offensive AA abilites that are worth getting early? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/stalrok/fullsize/stalroksig2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baruchthebarbarianbastard>baruch the barbarian bastard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/29/03 1:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3077.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA points, offense or defense?</span><hr size=1> Personally, I think some uber warrior should make a sticky similar to the "ubermob tanking" and "best hate" weapons dealing with some ideal AA paths to take. For us up-and-coming warriors, it would be literally the best thing wisdom could provide.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=629732" target="top">Babyblade the Froglok Bitch</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 263<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/29/03 3:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3077.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA points, offense or defense?</span><hr size=1> It depends on whether you're expected to tank often or not.  Unless your guild likes to lose their MTs, most of the warriors, ideally, would not get to tank very often at least versus ubers.  If you're not tanking, no amount of defense will help your guild.<br>
<br>
One thing to keep in mind that offensive skills makes the process of gaining any further AA faster (because you kill faster) while defensive AAs contribute very little to XP gain unless you're having trouble staying alive in XP groups.  Also more DPS is always stackable barring very few unmeleeable mobs.  If a mob dies 3 seconds faster due to your new offensive AAs, that's 3 seconds your healers don't have to heal.  Your 3 seconds might not make or break a raid, but put say 10 people's 3 seconds together and now a mob is suddenly dying half a minute faster which is significant.<br>
<br>
Punishing Blade, Tactical Mastery, and Ferocity are probably the best offensive AAs to get (PB obviously depends on the weapons you use).  PB and Ferocity also presumably gets you more aggro which is often more important than more defense or offense.  Although it's hard to prove offensive AAs help with aggro, defensive AAs most definitely don't make you aggro better for sure. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=weoden>Weoden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/29/03 4:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3077.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA points, offense or defense?</span><hr size=1> I never really tanked for my guild at all so i took aa that helped me xp.  I essentially took the cheaper aa so that I could get the benefits sooner.  In any case, combat stability, agility and fury are great aa to work on. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=92277"> Weo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Ret)Aaroan - Druid - Lv 60</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blloodsportfoehammer>Blloodsport Foehammer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.bluedeath.s5.com/images/smiley_ed.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/29/03 5:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3077.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bluedeath.s5.com/images/smiley_ed.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA points, offense or defense?</span><hr size=1> Depends on what you will be doing most of the time.<br>
<br>
If you are the guilds MT, or ST, then you must go deffensive.<br>
<br>
If you are like me, who is pretty low on the tank list, then get Offensive AAs. I have RF 1, PB 2, CF 3, and Ferocity 3 (for offensive) and get 140 - 150 dps on the back of a mob I am not tanking. I do this with a Windblade and about 1550 atk. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.bluedeath.s5.com/images/coollogo_com_105953167.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blloodsportfoehammer>Blloodsport Foehammer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.bluedeath.s5.com/images/smiley_ed.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/29/03 5:06:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pilerboy>pilerboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/30/03 1:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3077.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA points, offense or defense?</span><hr size=1> A lvl 65 warrior with maxed offensive aa will always lose to a lvl 65 warrior with maxed defensive aa, assuming the other variables (gear, buffs, etc) are equal.  Even if you are not a standard tank in your guild, you are going to benefit exp groups a lot more with defensive aa than offensive. who cares if you do an extra 300 damage per mob if the cleric has to cheal you an extra two times? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=193009"> Grendon's Stuff </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Member of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.familjen.dk">  Familjen </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Bristlebane Server<br>
<br>
&quot;Who ever heard of a hafling overlord, anyway?&quot;<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 265<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/30/03 1:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3077.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA points, offense or defense?</span><hr size=1> The extra benefit from defense AAs versus XP mobs is minuscule after you have your Archtype AAs done.  As for saying the cleric could've CHed you one less time... if you actually care about efficiency that much, you'd get a Shaman with Quiscence as your group's only healer instead of wasting a spot on a cleric.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A> at: 3/30/03 1:38:28 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thegiantone>TheGiantOne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/30/03 8:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3077.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA points, offense or defense?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>A lvl 65 warrior with maxed offensive aa will always lose to a lvl 65 warrior with maxed defensive aa, assuming the other variables (gear, buffs, etc) are equal. Even if you are not a standard tank in your guild, you are going to benefit exp groups a lot more with defensive aa than offensive. who cares if you do an extra 300 damage per mob if the cleric has to cheal you an extra two times?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Oh really?  LOL...Good thing you have never dueled me in the past.  Once upon a time when the world was born we had the first BotB on my server.  I had crap for gear and only good weapon I had was a Truncheon of Doom.  I took second place on my server with pure offensive skills against some of the best defensive gear warriors on my server.<br>
<br>
I agree that a warrior who is the MT in a guild should get defensive AA skills first but in places like PoV guess what the majority of exp groups I have joined like? DPS and more DPS and even more DPS.<br>
<br>
I have the following which gives me around 120 dps.<br>
Combat Fury 3<br>
Flurry 3<br>
Fury of the Ages 3<br>
Punishing Blade 3<br>
Double Riposte 2<br>
Ferocity 2<br>
Raging Flurry 2<br>
TM 2<br>
1550 attack<br>
Avatar (Self proc weapon)<br>
53/45 TSBS<br>
<br>
and maxed defensive 65 warrior (with no offensive AA) will beat me in a duel?<br>
<br>
And I don't have all my offensive AA skills maxed either.  See how you can't make blanket statements like the above?  A lot would depend on what weapons were allowed in the duel.  If you are talking about plain old swords 2h or 1h I would still kick the defensive warriors rear.<br>
<br>
But to make this short and sweet!  If an MT in any guild go for the defensive AA first.  If not the MT and you want in a lot of exp groups in say PoV definitely go for 2/3 offensive AA and 1/3 defensive AA because if you gonna want to do more damage then expect same from the mob who will hate you even more.<br>
<br>
I do about 7k - 10k damage average per mob in PoV.  So its more than an extra 300 damage per fight with the additional offensive AA skills.  So that without offensive AA would be 3600 to 6600 damage so the additional offensive damage done is an extra 2400 - 5400 per mob.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Marshall Gigantuous Carniverous<br>
65 Overlord of Povar<br>
105 AA and counting</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raunstoncutter>RaunStoncutter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 362<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/30/03 8:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3077.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/raunstonecutter/bunnyhop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA points, offense or defense?</span><hr size=1> For an up and comming, I would suggest ND3/AE taunt as your first ones, then after that, you make the choice:  are you raid MTing in the near future?  If the anwser is yes, go defensive, if not go offensive, fairly simple.<br>
<br>
I'd suggest getting punishing blade 1 though.  for two AA points, I increased my damage a good bit with 2h.  It's not too shabby =) <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31658">Raun Stonecutter</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.swordoffate.com">&lt;Sword of Fate&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
